<div class='commentbox'>
Wanted to comment from the perspective of someone who was on the first descent (I think?) in either<br/>
1986 or 87. Saw that the big falls near the end was called Compression Falls - we named that<br/>
Whammer Falls after Brian Wham who was first off that drop on that trip. At the bottom his helmet<br/>
was blown off and floated up first prompting Dale Adams to comment something like &quot;it tore his<br/>
f-ing head off&quot;. I think Dale was 2nd off the drop. We had a large group that day and had a great<br/>
trip ! I will never forget it ! Bob Vernon </div>
</td>
</tr>
