<div id='contact-148268'><span class='name'>Caleb Brauer</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/148268/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
We had some hard times on the lower Elk yesterday. We tried to portage Twisting Falls on the narrow<br/>
goat trail but didn't realize it was icy until we got up there. We wound up dropping our kayaks<br/>
into the falls and had to hike out of the gorge. I wanted to post this in case anyone sees our<br/>
kayaks or gear to let everyone know that we are ok. If you happen to find a couple of wavesport<br/>
diesel kayaks (blue and citrus) or some paddles, please email me (calebbrauer@yahoo.com) </div>
</td>
