<div class='commentbox'>
Hey Kevin, The falls near the end of the run, which I am calling &quot;compression falls&quot; can be run<br/>
anytime even when the gorge is not going. We found a trail that hikes down the side of the mtn and<br/>
almost right to it. You will still have to portage twisting falls due to the fact that is is almost<br/>
right above the drop. We go in there late november just to huck it for fun. Lowest ive went off is<br/>
58cfs. The pool is always good. Just remember to tuck!! </div>
</td>
